annotation.TEXT: Whoa, that probably wasn't the best choice of a level to Start+Select in, even though I still had plenty of time to.
It's not going to rain Ayas or some other nasty stuff down on me is it?

Now it's Reimu's turn to try that level. I just gotta get here all the way over there. Oh, and BTW, I've decided to stop watching Goron50's videos of this hack after his ninth episode for now, so I'll be going into the remaining levels blind. After I complete the game, I'll resume watching Goron's HAM videos.
Sanae demos: 9
Okay, I see what I'll need to do here. Watch out for the fire, and carefully aim the shell so that it hits the ON/OFF block. I'll only get one shot, so don't miss!
Although, I may need that itchy trigger finger if another quick-reaction thing comes up... Hmm... That's something to think about, actually...
I don't know what the deal was with those moles up there, though, since they just jumped straight out of bounds...
Okay, I'm going to possibly try something daring here... First, have Reimu max out Sanae's lives, then send Reimu into that level...
Oh, that's different. I auto-moved left after clearing that level, and the turn switched normally. Okay, Sanae, there's one SP Mission left, number 9. Can you handle it?

Whew! Too much power in that jump would've resulted in me being Kaizo trapped! Well, Sanae, I guess you can perform miracles too... (UPDATE: Actually, that wasn't really a miracle, as I would've been safe doing a standing spin jump into the goal moon regardless of how long I held A. However, a normal jump would've killed me.)
BGM: Super Nazo Puyo: Ruru no Ruu - Area 5 - Arle vs. Rulue (reused yet again)

I definitely had some close calls there (Showin' off yer 1337 grazin' skillz again, Reimu?), but now that things have calmed down a bit, this doesn't look like a terribly tricky level, outside of safely getting the balloon in the first place.
I wonder if the rest of these special levels will be even nastier...
Oh, that's an awesome score!
ARGH!!! And, apparently, the luck stops here.
Yeah, of course the Thwimp on the right is in the wrong sprite slot for me to take out with a Kisume, and I'm not even going to bother checking the left Thwimp.
BGM: Wonder Boy in Monster World - Final Dungeon (reused)
Woo, glad those fireballs weren't in the worst spots for me there! Now I just gotta reach the goal moon!
Oh, god. More precision swimming, and this time with cheepo Alices! Well, I've had good luck with the Alices in the past...
Okay, now next time, be more careful with that itchy trigger finger when a level starts. What if there was something like a death block right above my head?
To be continued...
Whoa, I felt like I nearly slipped at the end there... But I made it, and the rest is easy.
Ah, nuts. The turn didn't auto-switch. I guess I gotta do a Start+Select. (Also, I guess I'll balance out our lives.)
Oh, geez... Right away I see what needs to be done here!
SP Mission 8...
BGM: Super Nazo Puyo: Ruru no Ruu - Area 5 - Arle vs. Rulue (reused yet again)
BGM: Ievan Polkka (reused again)
Whoa, geez! Another quick-time event... But, ha! I reacted quickly enough this time, game! And, I should be able to get Sanae to finish this level... maybe.
BGM: Zelda: Twilight Princess - Secret Village (reused again)
I can definitely finish the job now without the balloon.
Yeah, I should totally be able to perform a 1-up combo here!
Whoa, whoops! I accidentally hit the A button as soon as the level started! Well, no time to think, so quickly grab the balloon and start bonking stuff!
And there's another auto-move left and proper turn switch. I wonder why they didn't do that for every level that needed it...
BGM: DKC2 - Stickerbrush Symphony (reused)
Yeah, no problems there.
So, what are the odds of Sanae getting the short end of the stick nine times in a row? Maybe 1 in 512?
Oh, man. This looks like it could be fun!
So, what insane challenges could these palm trees have for me? Find out next time, on quite possibly the finale, depending on how fast these palm tree levels go!
Hey there guys, and welcome back to Hakurei Adventure Mission! And now for the results of the vote...
Okay, now that I'm in the upper-left, I should be in a good position to stomp a bunch of Alices in a row for lives.
And we're done! Good thing I didn't accidentally make the level unwinnable!
SP Mission... 7? Huh? That's not right. Where's 6?
Move faster, pumpkinhead! ...Ehh, that doesn't quite have the same ring to it as "Move faster, Pokey!"...
Okay, I'm running out of time, and I don't want to press my luck way too much and risk getting whammied! Let's settle for that 3-life combo.
SP Mission 5...
Too bad I didn't have the foresight to transfer a life to Reimu to max her out before entering here, but that's okay. I'm sure I'll be able to pick up a 1-up somewhere.
Boing, boing, boing! Well, at least I didn't need to react "instantly" here.
That's odd. I wonder why they put 6 up here?
Ah, so that's why that overhang is there like that, so that the Alices I happen to stomp during the victory march won't Kaizo trap me!
In fact, I don't even think the balloon is strictly required (though it certainly makes stomping these duders easier).
Looks like it so far. Now, for my daring (and possibly idiotic) move-- I'm going to try to life farm here!!!
...That is, unless there are more levels that I don't know about. If there are more levels than these remaining, let me know!
BGM: Star Fox 2 - Fortuna Underground Base (reused)
Oh, um... I'm going to need to perform the tiniest jump that I can here. Now to tap A very briefly...
BGM: Diddy Kong Racing - Star City (reused again)
Umm... nothing...?
Sanae demos: 8
Okay, now that the ultra fast Yukkuris are out of here, I can take it easy.
Oh, man. Glancing down below, it looks like I'll have to make a mad dash on the home stretch...
Holy cow! I just barely made it! Alright, that could count as another miracle for Sanae!
WAH!!! ...I needed to react ultra quickly there... And, of course, Sanae's the one that's unfortunate enough to be put in that situation again.

Just gotta be sure I'm always descending when I'm stomping them. I wouldn't want to be killed by the "ascending" glitch (where, if I'm moving upwards when I hit an enemy, the game will typically decide that I get hurt instead of the enemy, even if I'm above a stompable enemy).
Alright, Sanae. Can you do SP Mission 2?
But, man, reaching that ON/OFF block and coming back alive is going to be tricky...
5-life combo!
BGM: TMNT NES - Area 5's Buildings and Caves
Woo, that was tight! Also, I'm surprised that those Thwimps haven't had their graphics changed.
Okay, Sanae, you can handle SP Mission 7, I just know it!
SP Mission 3...
BGM: Fire Emblem - Together We Ride
Well, whatever. It's nice to have a breather level every once in a while anyway.
Okay, no quick-time events here, and actually, this level looks pretty simple. I wonder what that ON/OFF block is for, though...
Whoa, fire. But, at least I can take a moment to look over the level from the starting point this time.
Okay, the Yukari gap levels are done, so that just leaves the four palm tree levels and the final level!
Okay, get ready to run like heck, Sanae!
Oh, man. We've got a diagonal bullet generator in addition to everything else here? Well, I should still be able to handle this. Those Kisumes over there might be a bit tricky to get past, though.
Whoa, close call with that Remilia up there. Also, I'm going to need to bounce off something to reach her.
Alright, Reimu, I hope you've got quick reflexes!
Now for SP Mission 4, which is down here.
Well, that was weird... This level was pretty easy, but that ON/OFF block puzzles me. Is it just a red herring, or was it actually meant to do something meaningful here?

1 vote for spiky guy, 1 vote for me to play Minecraft, 1 vote to get Reimu and Sanae to create a popular TV talk show with Mario appearing as a guest, 1 vote to get both Reimu and Sanae back up to 99 lives using any life-farming level (maybe I'll do that at some point), 2 votes for world 3 (including one 3-1 vote), 1 vote for the final level, 8 votes for the palm tree levels, and 16 votes for the Yukari gap levels! So, here I go, starting with the first of the Yukari gap levels!
Okay, now will Reimu have better luck against the Alice brigade?
Yeah! Now just simply climb up to the goal moon! I assume that red spiky guy will support me during the victory march, right?
I just hope that the possibly glitchy corners of the custom blocks don't somehow screw me over...
